# Preparation

## VSCode

Go to the [VSCode website](https://code.visualstudio.com/) and download/install the latest version of the editor.

## Windowns terminal

* Go to the [Microsoft Store](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/windows-terminal/9n0dx20hk701) for the Windows Terminal.
* Click `View in Store`.
* Install the Windows Terminal in the Microsoft Store.

## Enable WSL

Open PowerShell as Administrator and run the following command:

```powershell
wsl --install --distribution Ubuntu-24.04
```

Allow adminsitrator access when you see pop-up window.

## Set-up Ubuntu

Open the Windows Terminal from start menu, and click the down arrow on the top bar. Select `Ubuntu-24.04` from the dropdown menu. It will take a few minutes to install the Ubuntu.

After it finishes, set username and password for the Ubuntu. Note: when you type the password you do not see anything. Just type and press enter.



